benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/payments - Retrieve account payments

covered: Valid Request coverage (TC01) with 200 responses for existing account
Empty response handling for accounts with no payments (TC08) and non-existent accounts (TC09)

Query parameter coverage (TC02 withAttempts, TC03 withPluginInfo, TC04 pluginProperty, TC05 audit FULL, TC06 audit MINIMAL, TC07 all combined, TC14 with unsupported parameter, TC17 malformed pluginProperty, TC18 invalid audit value)
Authentication/Authorization scenarios (TC11 missing token, TC12 expired/invalid token)
Performance and scale considerations (TC15 large data volume)
Regression scenarios (TC21 withAttempts=false, TC22 backward compatibility, TC25 partially populated data)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not explicitly tested (no dedicated pagination parameters like page/size)
Explicit rate limiting/throttling tests are missing
Detailed authorization/permission edge cases beyond 401 (e.g., 403) not covered
Explicit ordering/pagination edge cases (limit/offset interactions) not covered
recommendations: Add dedicated pagination tests to verify correct behavior with page/size, total counts, and proper ordering.
Add caching tests to validate ETag/Cache-Control headers and client-side caching implications.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure proper handling under load or burst scenarios.
Include edge-case authorization tests that distinguish between 401/403 and cover permission-bound access if applicable.
Add more explicit tests for boundary conditions on pluginProperty parameter (e.g., extremely long values, special characters) and their impact on performance.
